Q1) wap in c to create  a TCP socket through which client will send a string to the server, 
and server will echo back the string to the client. When client will send exit then server 
will drop the connection

Q2) wap in c to create a TCP socket throgh which client will send an integer number to the server. 
Server will return back the reverse of that number to the client.

Q3) wap in c to create a TCP socket throgh which client will send an integer array to the server.
Server will sort the array in ascending order and return back to the client.
